,0,'revision','',0),(289,1,'2018-01-16 19:17:27','2018-01-16 19:17:27','General layout in theme is page.xml. Other xml layout just overwrites it.\r\n\r\nSuppose our page.xml looks like this:\r\n<pre class=\"EnlighterJSRAW\" data-enlighter-language=\"null\">&lt;layout version=\"0.1.0\"&gt;\r\n\r\n    &lt;default translate=\"label\" module=\"page\"&gt;\r\n        &lt;label&gt;All Pages&lt;/label&gt;\r\n        &lt;block type=\"page/html\" name=\"root\" output=\"toHtml\" template=\"page/3columns.phtml\"&gt;\r\n\r\n            &lt;block type=\"page/html_head\" name=\"head\" as=\"head\"&gt;\r\n                &lt;action method=\"addJs\"&gt;&lt;script&gt;prototype/prototype.js&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/action&gt;\r\n            &lt;/block&gt;\r\n        &lt;/block&gt;\r\n    &lt;/default&gt;\r\n&lt;/layout&gt;\r\n</pre>\r\n&lt;block ... &gt; - what is it? It is block that we can replace. About it later.\r\n\r\ntype=\"page/html\" - what is it? It is block type)\r\n\r\nWhere \"page\" - it is short name for Mage_Page_Block (path to block files). This name is define in the config.xml in Mage/Page/etc/config.xml :\r\n<pre class=\"EnlighterJSRAW\" data-enlighter-language=\"null\">&lt;config&gt;\r\n    ...\r\n    &lt;global&gt;\r\n        ...\r\n        &lt;blocks&gt;\r\n            &lt;page&gt;\r\n                &lt;class&gt;Mage_Page_Block&lt;/class&gt;\r\n            &lt;/page&gt;\r\n        &lt;/blocks&gt;\r\n        ...\r\n    &lt;/global&gt;\r\n    ....\r\n&lt;/config&gt;</pre>\r\nAnd where \"html\" - it is short name for class Mage_Page_Block_Html, which lies in the folder Mage/Page/Block/Html.php\r\n\r\nWait a minute. page.xml also has &lt;block type=\"page/html_head\" ... &gt; , but we don\'t have a file Mage/Page/Block/Html_head.php.\r\n\r\nYes, undercsore can be instead of \"/\", and \"type\" now points to the file Mage/Page/Block/Html/Head.php\r\n\r\n- Ok, ok. What means&lt;action method=\"addJs\"&gt; in&lt;block type=\"page/html_head\" ... &gt;?\r\n\r\nIt is just method in class Head.php that will be called. Check, this class or his parent has this method:\r\n<pre class=\"EnlighterJSRAW\" data-enlighter-language=\"null\">public function addJs($name, $params = \"\")\r\n{\r\n   $this-&gt;addItem(\'js\', $name, $params);\r\n   return $this;\r\n}</pre>\r\n- Ok, even i understood. But what means&lt;block ... template=\"page/3columns.phtml\"&gt;\r\n\r\nIt is just url to template file that lies in app/design/frontend/base/default/template/page/3columns.phtml\r\n\r\n- What means&lt;block ... name=\"root\" ... &gt; ?\r\n\r\nJust name of block. Need for to appeal to him, or override him.\r\n\r\n--------------------- How i can add my template (later)\r\n\r\n- Can we owerride some block in our template?\r\n\r\nYes, just in your template create block with same name to override him.\r\n<pre class=\"EnlighterJSRAW\" data-enlighter-language=\"null\">...\r\n&lt;checkout_onepage_index translate=\"label\"&gt;\r\n        &lt;label&gt;One Page Checkout&lt;/label&gt;\r\n        &lt;!-- Mage_Checkout --&gt;\r\n        &lt;remove name=\"left\"/&gt;\r\n\r\n        &lt;block type=\"insurance/mycontent\" name=\"root\" template=\"insurance/mycontent.phtml\"/&gt;\r\n&lt;/checkout_onepage_index&gt;\r\n...</pre>\r\nNow in page /checkout/onepage/index all \"root\" block will be replace on mycontent.phtml. Naturally, it is necessary that there existed type=\"insurance/mycontent\" and template=\"insurance/mycontent.phtml\".\r\n\r\n- Can i remove block, without change it?\r\n\r\nYes, just writte &lt;remove name=\"root\"&gt;\r\n\r\n- Can i add information to block, without delete existing code.\r\n\r\nYes, just writte:\r\n<pre class=\"EnlighterJSRAW\" data-enlighter-language=\"null\">&lt;reference name=\"root\"&gt;\r\n     &lt;block type=\"insurance/mycontent\" name=\"didididi\" template=\"insurance/list.phtml\"/&gt;\r\n&lt;/reference&gt;</pre>\r\nAnd after that, your block with name=\"didididi\" will be added to the end block with name=\"root\".\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n